00:12:26.010 --> 00:12:27.709 align:middle line:90%
at the back of the room.

00:12:27.709 --> 00:12:29.250 align:middle line:84%
I knew they weren't
afraid, they were

00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:33.000 align:middle line:84%
watching, because they'd never
seen so many children and toys

00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:33.960 align:middle line:90%
in one place.

00:12:33.960 --> 00:12:36.870 align:middle line:84%
But both times, the teachers
walked up to them and said,

00:12:36.870 --> 00:12:39.090 align:middle line:90%
oh, are you afraid, are you shy.

00:12:39.090 --> 00:12:42.060 align:middle line:84%
And so those labels
kind of fell onto them.

00:12:42.060 --> 00:12:46.410 align:middle line:84%
So labels of fearfulness
and all these difficulties

00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:48.970 align:middle line:84%
are applied to sensitive people,
even when they don't apply.

00:12:48.970 --> 00:12:54.820 align:middle line:10%
>> If you identify kids that
show a particular behavior,

00:12:54.820 --> 00:12:57.630 align:middle line:10%
and the behavior
might be very quiet,

00:12:57.630 --> 00:13:02.610 align:middle line:10%
